ce:section.ce:para:
The microstructure of the conducting CDs-PSS-Na and nanofluid of CDs-PSS-M2070 was identified by JEOL-2100 transmission electron microscopy (TEM). The NICOLET 6700 fourier transform infrared spectrometer (FTIR) was used to characterize the chemical structure of CDs-PSS-Na and CDs-PSS-M2070, and the related XRD patterns were obtained by D8 ADVANCE X-ray diffraction analyzer (XRD). The chemical compositions of CDs-PSS-Na and CDs-PSS-M2070 were identified by the Axis Ultra X-ray photoelectron spectrometer (XPS). The thermal stability of CDs-PSS-Na and CDs-PSS-M2070 was analyzed by a Diamond thermal gravimetric analyzer in a flowing Argon between 50 and 700 °C (10 °C /min). The glass transition temperature (T

                           g
                        ) and melting point (T

                           m
                        ) of CDs-PSS-M2070 were obtained by NETZSCH differential scanning calorimeter (DSC).
